data.enText: several events or things of a similar kind that happen one after the other

data.chText: 那一事件引发出一连串谁都没有料到的事。
data.enText: The incident sparked off a whole series of events that nobody had foreseen.

data.chText: 论现代社会性质的一系列文章中最新的一篇
data.enText: the latest in a series of articles on the nature of modern society

data.chText: （广播或电视上题材或角色相同的）系列节目
data.enText: a set of radio or television programmes that deal with the same subject or that have the same characters
a set of sports games played between the same two teams

data.chText: 世界系列美国职业棒球锦标赛
英格兰板球队在同印度队的系列比赛中落败。
data.enText: England have lost the Test series (= of cricket matches) against India.
an electrical circuit in which the current passes through all the parts in the correct order

means: (广播或电视上题材或角色相同的)系列节目

ex.chText: 一连串不幸事件使他焦头烂额。
ex.enText: A sequence of misfortunes have plagued him.

ex.chText: 本文按历史顺序论述那些事件。
ex.enText: The paper deals with the events in historical sequence.

ex.chText: 他按事情发生的先后次序解释那些情况。
ex.enText: He explained the facts in the sequence of events.

synonyms.bx: 指事物衔接的次序，可以是发生的先后顺序，也可以是逻辑顺序。

ex.chText: 事故引起了一连串事件。
ex.enText: The accident caused a chain of events.

ex.chText: 他们的行为在全国引发了一系列叛乱。
ex.enText: Their acts set off a chain of revolts throughout the country.

ex.chText: 这一连串事件或许会导致又一场战争。
ex.enText: The chain of events might lead to another war.

synonyms.bx: 指像链条一样连接在一起的一连串事物，有时彼此间含因果关系。

ex.enText: They've had a series of good harvests.

ex.chText: 她听了关于科幻小说写作的系列讲座。
ex.enText: She attended a series of lectures about science fiction writing.

ex.chText: 反对歧视的一系列法规已经颁布。
ex.enText: A series of laws against discrimination have been issued.

ex.chText: 这一荒诞的学说是以一系列错误的设想为依据的。
ex.enText: This ridiculous theory is based on a series of wrong assumptions.

synonyms.bx: 强调是同类事物，可以前后互有关联，也可以各成独立的单位。

ex.chText: 他们取得了一个接一个的胜利。
ex.enText: They won a succession of victories.

ex.chText: 他的话连珠炮似地说了出来。
ex.enText: His words came out in quick succession.

ex.chText: 接连不断的聚会把他们累垮了。
ex.enText: The endless succession of parties wore them out.

synonyms.bx: 强调同类事物或事件的相继出现或发生，侧重于一个接一个的次序，其中并非含有一定的逻辑性。

tr: (mathematics) the sum of a finite or infinite sequence of expressions
a periodical that appears at scheduled times
(sports) several contests played successively by the same teams
example: the visiting team swept the series

tr: similar things placed in order or happening one after another
example: they were investigating a series of bank robberies

tr: a group of postage stamps having a common theme or a group of coins or currency selected as a group for study or collection
example: the Post Office issued a series commemorating famous American entertainers
his coin collection included the complete series of Indian-head pennies

tr: (electronics) connection of components in such a manner that current flows first through one and then through the other
example: the voltage divider consisted of a series of fixed resistors

value.def: A series of things or events is a number of them that come one after the other.

example.ex: ...a series of meetings with students and political leaders.
example.tran: 与学生和政治领袖的一系列会面

value.tran: 一连串;一系列;连续;接连

value.def: A radio or television series is a set of programmes of a particular kind which have the same title.

example.ex: ...the TV series 'The Trials of Life' presented by David Attenborough.
example.tran: 由戴维·阿滕伯勒主持的电视系列片《生命之源》

example.ex: ...the world's longest-running radio series, Britain's 'The Archers'.
example.tran: 世界上最长的广播剧，英国的《阿彻一家》

value.tran: (广播或电视的)系列节目,系列片

value.boxu_tran: 注意不要混淆 series 和 serial。
value.boxu_usage: Take care not to confuse series and serial
